[The level of vaccination in Byron Bay is extremely low and unsurprisingly the number of measles cases is high. Cases of SSPE as a result of measles virus infection are rare.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Australia can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/1z_*.
Byron Bay is a beachside town located in the far-northeastern corner of the state of New South Wales, Australia. It is located 772 km (480 mi) north of Sydney and 165 km (103 mi) south of Brisbane. Cape Byron, a headland adjacent to the town, is the easternmost point of mainland Australia. At the 2006 Census, the town had a permanent population of 4981.
A map of New South Wales showing the location of Byron Bay can be accessed at http://www.merimbula.org/realty/198/nsw-map.html. - Mod.CP]

